Ed: Your idea of a separate thread regarding PTSD is excellant and needs to be done. Why don't you start it?  Delayed Onset is definately a recognized &quot;by the so called experts&quot;  form of PTSD. So is Childhood Origins, and the real culprit, just plain ol PTSD.<br><br>
Cook: In a last effort to &quot;come clean&quot; between us, state your most important 5 questions or charges at me, I will answer them in no bullshit language, OK?  I can't think of anything more fair than that, unless we play turn-about. Whatcha say?  Of course, I recognize the difference between murder, something civilians do to each other, and killing the enemy, something done in war. Please, PLEASE do not lable me wrongly. I do not fault any American draftee or enlisted man who killed any enemy, political or actual. That was your sworn duty, to your government, and whether your government was right, or in this case, wrong, you did what you had to do. I do not throw stones. I do not make moral judgements. If I was in the jungle, I doubt that there would be a clip long enough to give me security as I would never stop pulling the trigger.  I have learned to have nothing but admiration for you who survived the jungle. Politics be damned. You are a gutsy and brave bunch of guys. The issue of whether you should have been there or not, is a different topic to the fact that you survived.<br><br>
Cook, what is it with you that you must distort what I say, change what I say, and duck my questions to you?  I could be your non-enemy, but you seem to have a issue with me no matter what I say, or what you think I said.  I think the problem is you, my man, not me. Think about it!!! A word search does not prove a damn thing.  I do not think of you as a murderer or a baby killer. PERIOD. Is that clear enough for you to understand.  Damn, you are the most thick headed person I have ever met, and I have met more than my fair share.  <br><br>
Welcome back John. If we are going to get into the real issues, I would like to ask all of you the following:<br><br>
1. How does PTSD affect you (if you have it)?  How does or did it F*** up your life?<br><br>
2. Agent Orange: Fact or fiction? Is it real or B.S.? Most civilians don't know, and the ones that see the bums on the freeway on ramps saying &quot;agent orange-viet viet-will work for food, do the worst P.R. for the real agenda.  What is you guys (pardon the bad grammer) experience with this?<br><br>
Cook, interesting that you want to play football (above post) now that we are getting serious. I hope that was a mis-read on my part and not a tactic on your part to steer people away from serious issues.  The WWW makes name calling all too easy, and serious discussion and answers can get lost. I hope not.<br><br>
Cook, it is a big lake we both fish in. And there is no absolute right or wrong. At the end of the day we can weigh the fist and see who is the better fisherman, but we will never know who is the most stylish, the most intellectual, the most knowledgeable, so why don't we forget all that crap, and just fish, and maybe, share some bait?<br>

